{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771588933,"nonce":"E2VonqOKqRlCiLJefdyU4fWxs0E=","title":"Early data minimization for inactive borrowers within retention period","message":"Borrowers who left the university but have lending history within the 7-year retention window keep all personal data (phone, student ID, full name) for the entire retention period. This is more data than necessary.\n\nConsider a two-stage approach:\n1. After 24 months of inactivity: strip non-essential fields (phone, student ID) while keeping name and email for identification\n2. After 7 years: full anonymization as currently implemented\n\nThis would better satisfy GDPR data minimization (Article 5(1)(c)) while still meeting HGB §257 accounting requirements. The lending records only need a linkable identity, not the borrower's phone number.","files":null}]}